Light sources

At night, the poorest homes have no light or any reliable light source, restricting how productive the family can be. Low to middle income homes use bare light bulbs to illuminate the home. The richest have diverse and personalised lighting in each room of their home, with sophisticated light dimmers and light shades. Read more >>

Home About Team Donate Photographers

Dollar Street is a Gapminder project - free for anyone to use.

Today we feature more than 300 homes in 56 countries.

In total we have more than 30 000 photos, and counting! 

 

Want to add a home? There are still lots of places in the world not represented on Dollar Street. You can find all the resources for documenting a home here.
